projects.description:
Deputy team leader, river engineer, GIS expert and team coordinator of sub-consultants in this study. The Jangwani valley in Dar Es Salaam, and its surrounding wards, is a highly flood‐prone area. During high flow events of the Msimbazi River, Morogoro Road and Jangwani Bridge get flooded, making the crossing of the valley impossible. The Bus Rapid Transport (BRT) depot located just next to the Jangwani Bridge also get flooded regularly damaging not only the depot’s structures and obstructing the drainage system, but also the parked busses inside.
The Tanzania National Roads Agency (TANROADS) has commissioned CDR International BV in association with Stichting Deltares and WEMA Consultants to carry out consultancy services consisting of three stages;
‐ Stage 1: Studies and Preliminary Designs;
‐ Stage 2: Surveys, Detailed Design and Tender Documents. Main measure is the raising and widening of an existing bridge to a length of 400m;
‐ Stage 3: Scoping for Environmental and Social Impact Assessments.
Client: TANROADS (World Bank funded)
